02/09/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Lidija Topic has declined to become the head of BiH's Directorate of European Integration, local media reported on Tuesday (September 1st). 
She was supposed to take over on Monday. 
No official reason for her decision was given. 
The State Service Agency is appointing Nevenka Savic in her place. 
She is due to take office on September 15th. 
The post has been vacant since January, when then-Director Osman Topcagic was appointed as BiH's Ambassador to Brussels. 
(BHRT, Dnevni Avaz, Srna, RTRS - 01/09/09)
